               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183706120028"></xptr>
               <p>to the prisoner—he was doubling it up—when I seized him he turned and strack me in the breast—I pursued, and took him—he got from me again, went oil, and threw the handkerchief down in the middle of the raad—I still followed, and retook him—a person picked up the handker<lb></lb>chief and gave it to me—I never lost sight of the prisoner, away from me several times.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I was going to deliver some letters for a friend and was seen ✗ by a female with whom I had some acquaintances—we had some refreshment, and she was joined by other acquaintances—I was going on when the policeman seized me, and said I was his prisoner, and asked what I had done with the handkerchief—he forced his hand into my pockety and took out none—during that time a man brought up this handkerchief—the pre<lb></lb>secutor said it was his, and I was taken.</p>
